Excessive requirements for public procurement applications shall be excluded by law
The legislation may establish exhaustive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session at the plenary session of the State Duma, they plan to consider in the second reading a draft law establishing requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, the participants of which can only be small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities".
The bill was developed in accordance with the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium-Sized Enterprises in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to request as part of the application from procurement participants - small and medium-sized enterprises.
And also - about the list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the Law "On Procurement of Goods, Works and Services by Certain Types of Legal Entities" regulates the procurement activities of certain types of legal entities.
The requirements for the content, form, registration and composition of the application for participation in the procurement shall be established by the customers independently in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, customers establish redundant requirements for the content, registration of the application, the mandatory presence in its composition of certificates, certificates, extracts, the period of receipt of which in the authorized bodies is comparable with the period of submission of applications, which leads to the impossibility of participation in such a purchase and a reduction in the number of participants in the purchase", - it is stated in the explanation to the draft law.
The new bill provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to demand in the application from procurement participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises.
"The adoption of the document will exclude arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises," the explanatory note says.
