The authorities of the Moscow region told about the fate of closed landfills
In the Moscow region, the landfills of solid household waste continue to be closed.
This year, the authorities promise to eliminate the latter.
Some of the 39 existing landfills are being upgraded to modern waste treatment complexes.
But this option is not possible for every polygon - many of them overgrown with dense residential development.
After the polygon is closed, it stands up for reclamation - the body of the polygon is overflowing with soils, systems of degassing and infiltration are installed.
This allows you to stop the chemical processes inside the landfill, so that it does not ignite, does not emit odors, does not poison the soil and groundwater.
And then the former landfill remains to rise a useless pile among the surrounding residential buildings.
Why not make something useful out of it?
For example, in Ruza, where the reclamation of the site "Annino" just recently ended, the authorities are considering the option of making a pile of ski slopes.
This landfill, operated from 1976 to 2016, grew so that it went beyond the boundaries of the land allocated for it.
Therefore, during the reclamation, it was necessary to buy out neighboring plots, de facto long ago already clogged with garbage.
"Some time will pass, the polygon will "saddle", will gain strength, and we will think what can be done to make it begin to benefit.
Directly catches the eye - the ski resort," - said the head of the Ruz district Nikolay Parfenov.
