A Rwandan man confessed to setting fire to a cathedral in Nantes
A Rwandan man who worked at St. Peter and Paul’s Cathedral in the French city of Nantes on a voluntary basis confessed to his arson a week after the fire.
This is reported on Sunday by the TV channel "France-3".
According to him, the man, who was already detained on July 19, the day after the fire, was detained again the day before.
