However, according to CCTV footage, he left the religious institution 15 minutes after receiving calls about the fire in the building.
The fire in the Cathedral of Saints Peter and Paul occurred on July 18.
More than 200 firefighters fought for a monument of Gothic architecture for several hours.
However, they failed to save the stained glass windows of the time of Louis XII and the unique organ of the Baroque era.
The situation was brought under control only three hours after the start of the fire.
As a result of the accident, no one was injured.
The current fire is not the first in the history of the temple.
In 1972, a fire destroyed his roof.
It took 13 years to eliminate the effects of that fire.
For parishioners, the cathedral was reopened only in 1985.
