Degtyarev was surprised by the information on the purchase of gas "Sakhalin-1" for dollars
The acting governor of the Khabarovsk Territory Mikhail Degtyarev on Sunday, July 26, during a meeting with residents of Soviet Havana was surprised that the region is buying Sakhalin gas produced by the American company Exxon Neftegas, for dollars.
American gas is contracted in dollars until 2025.
“To be honest, I didn’t know that, and I’m in such a knockdown because of this information.
I had no idea that this was still possible in 2020 in Russia,” he told RIA Novosti.
Degtyarev noted that this issue was discussed with the head of the Russian Energy Ministry Alexander Novak during his visit to Khabarovsk on July 24.
The governor also stressed that by 2025, Gazprom will switch to supply Russian thermal power plants and capacities, which means that Russian gas purchased in rubles “at normal prices” will be used.
The Sakhalin-1 project is implemented through a production-sharing agreement, where Exxon Neftegas Ltd is the project operator with a 30% share, another 20% from Rosneft, Sodeco 30% from Japan and ONGC 20% from India.
The Khabarovsk Territory has been acquiring gas from this project since 2005.
